I found the issue. In both `graph_2d.dart:79` and `graph_3d.dart:88`, the `shouldRepaint` method is comparing object references:

```dart
bool shouldRepaint(covariant _ProjectilePainter oldDelegate) {
  return oldDelegate.model != model;
}
```

Since the same `model` instance is passed, this always returns `false`, so the graph never repaints when slider values change.

The fix is to compare the actual values that affect rendering:

